<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFACFFBFC6A457E5FE0DF951" box="[151,384,1750,1777]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFACFFBFC6A457E5FE0DF951" blockId="24.[151,655,1714,1777]" box="[151,384,1750,1777]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
(
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFACFFBFC6AC57E5FEA0F951" box="[159,301,1750,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Figs. 18A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFACFFBFC70B57E5FEF5F951" box="[312,376,1750,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[215,1385,223,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-22@34.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 25A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females. A–B. P. rudisetosus Disney et Michailovskaya; C–D. P. pullum Michailovskaya; E–F. P. obtusatus Liu et Cai; G–H. P. linzhiensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. shennongjianus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559617/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">25I–J</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFACFFBDC6A4562DFE0FFF59" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFACFFBFC6A4562DFBE5F868" blockId="24.[151,1436,1822,1993]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFACFFBFC6A4562DFE9FF898" bold="true" box="[151,274,1822,1848]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta shorter than maximum width of palpus; tarsomere 5 shorter than tarsomere 1; setal palisade 3/4 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 3 short setulae in transverse row; sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFACFFBFC7FD56B9FDBEF805" box="[462,563,1930,1957]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-22@20.[151,1436,179,1367]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Pseudacteon pullum Disney et Michailovskaya, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559576/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
) forms a narrow strip and two small pieces behind it; dorsum of oviscape with about 6–7 minute setulae each side; venter of oviscape with 2 minute setulae each side.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFADFFBEC6A45455FADCFA02" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" startId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" targetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFADFFBEC6A45455FADCFA02" blockId="25.[151,1436,1382,1442]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFADFFBEC6A45455FED6FADE" bold="true" box="[151,347,1382,1406]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">FIGURES 18A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFADFFBEC7525455FD05FADE" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[353,648,1382,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFADFFBEC7525455FD05FADE" box="[353,648,1382,1406]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Pseudacteon shennongjianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFADFFBEC4BD5455FD52FADE" bold="true" box="[654,735,1382,1406]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFADFFBEC4BD5455FD52FADE" box="[654,735,1382,1406]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFADFFBEC6F454E3FF64F93E" blockId="25.[151,1437,1488,2019]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFADFFBEC6F454E3FEA8FA4A" bold="true" box="[199,293,1488,1514]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFADFFBEC7F554E3FDE2FA4B" box="[454,623,1488,1515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.44" metricValueMax="1.45" metricValueMin="1.43" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="1.44" valueMax="1.45" valueMin="1.43">1.43–1.45 mm</quantity>
. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC4FC54E3FCBAFA4A" box="[719,823,1488,1514]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
) yellow, with 14–16 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, upper pair being higher on frons than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta directly under lower fronto-orbital seta. Second row of frontal setae clearly concave, with upper interfronal setae further from each other than either is from upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 yellow and subglobose. Palpus pale yellow, with 6 long setae, apical one shorter than maximum of width of palpus. Labrum and labella pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFADFFBEC6F4579BFBC6F8D6" blockId="25.[151,1437,1488,2019]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Thorax yellow. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior four times length of anterior. Legs pale yellow. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 1.05: 0.73: 0.71: 0.66: 1, with all five bearing a setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC31A57FFFA02F946" box="[1321,1423,1740,1766]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade extends 3/4 (0.72) length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC4D557C3FCC3F8AA" box="[742,846,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur a little shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC4AE5627FC8FF88E" box="[669,770,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC5575627FC45F88E" box="[868,968,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFADFFBEC2145627FB00F88F" box="[1063,1165,1812,1839]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.40 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFADFFBEC2D25627FAC5F88F" box="[1249,1352,1812,1839]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="0.71">0.71 mm</quantity>
, width/ length 0.51. Costal index 0.40. Costal ratios 1.71: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFADFFBEC56E560BFB96F8F3" box="[861,1051,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.65" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="0.0565" valueMax="0.058" valueMin="0.055">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFADFFBEC56E560BFC11F8F3" box="[861,924,1848,1875]" degrees="0.055" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" precision="55" value="0.055">0.055</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFADFFBEC5AF560BFC64F8F3" box="[924,1001,1848,1875]" degrees="0.058" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" precision="55" value="-0.058">–0.058</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Costa with 14 dorsal setulae. Alula with 4 setae. Veins slightly yellow, membrane hyaline. Haltere whitish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFADFFBDC6F456B3FBE2FF75" blockId="25.[151,1437,1488,2019]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Abdominal tergites yellow and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae on posterior margins. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC35C56B3FF30F81F" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[215,1385,223,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-22@34.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 25A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females. A–B. P. rudisetosus Disney et Michailovskaya; C–D. P. pullum Michailovskaya; E–F. P. obtusatus Liu et Cai; G–H. P. linzhiensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. shennongjianus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559617/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 25I</figureCitation>
) reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 3 short setulae in transverse row. Venter pale yellow. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFADFFBEC7CF56FBFDDAF843" box="[508,599,1992,2019]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[215,1385,223,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-22@34.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 25A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females. A–B. P. rudisetosus Disney et Michailovskaya; C–D. P. pullum Michailovskaya; E–F. P. obtusatus Liu et Cai; G–H. P. linzhiensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. shennongjianus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559617/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 25J</figureCitation>
) forms a narrow strip, behind it there are two small sclerotized pieces, each with 2 long setulae, and 2–3 short setulae in outside of pieces. The dorsum of the oviscape with about 6–7 minute setulae each side. The venter of the oviscape with 2 minute setulae each side (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAEFFBDC5CC5188FBEFFF75" box="[1023,1122,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 18" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-19@25.[151,1435,179,1355]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 18A–F. Pseudacteon shennongjianus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterio view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559593/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAEFFBDC6F451ECFE0FFF59" blockId="26.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[199,386,223,249]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC6F451ECFE86FF59" bold="true" box="[199,267,223,249]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Male.</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFAEFFBDC6F45031FD9DFEBE" box="[199,528,258,286]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" type="distribution">
