<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFAEFFBDC6F4505CFBE2FE55" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAEFFBDC6F4505CFBE2FE55" blockId="26.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC6F4505CFEB6FE29" bold="true" box="[199,315,367,393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species seems similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFAEFFBDC4FA505CFCE1FE28" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[713,876,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tianmuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC4FA505CFCE1FE28" box="[713,876,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">P. tianmuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC546505CFC5DFE29" bold="true" box="[885,976,367,393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFAEFFBDC546505CFC5DFE29" box="[885,976,367,393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, it differs from the latter by longer setal palisade of mid tibia and shorter apical seta of palpus. In the key to Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFAEFFBDC24250A0FF5EFE71" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." pageId="26" pageNumber="227" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">Disney &amp; Michailovskaya 2000</bibRefCitation>
), the new species runs to couplets 3 to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFAEFFBDC4AA5084FB36FE71" authority="Disney et Michailovskaya, 2000" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="2000" box="[665,1211,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setipalpatus">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC4AA5084FCB3FE71" box="[665,830,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">P. setipalpatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFAEFFBDC5745084FB36FE71" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[839,1211,439,465]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">
Disney 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC5935084FC39FE70" box="[928,948,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">et</emphasis>
Michailovskaya, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but is immediately distinguished from the latter by yellowish body colour and shorter apical seta of palpus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
